  "instructions": [
    "Combine vinegar and lemon juice in a small bowl.",
    "Add olive oil, red pepper flakes, salt, and chopped fresh parsley to the vinegar-lemon mixture.",
    "Whisk until well combined. Set aside.",
    "Pat dry beef fillets with paper towels.",
    "Season both sides of the beef with a pinch of salt.",
    "Heat broiler to high heat.",
    "Place beef fillet on a greased baking sheet or grill pan.",
    "Brush beef with prepared sauce, making sure it's evenly distributed over the surface.",
    "Broil for 4-5 minutes per side or until juices run clear and external temperature reaches at least 145°F (63°C).",
    "Garnish with freshly minced ginger.",
    "Serve immediately."
